project tradesdb {
  database_type: 'postgresql'
  note: '''
  # Algorithmic Trading Database (tradesdb)

  Operational store for automated / algorithmic trading executed through
  broker API platforms. Holds the trading domain - brokers, accounts,
  strategies, capital allocations, the tradable universe, and risk rules -
  plus the append-mostly fact stream of signals, orders, executions, position
  snapshots, daily P&L, circuit-breaker events, and an immutable audit log.

  Reference data (currency, securities, exchanges, derivative contracts) is
  **not** mastered here; it arrives read-only via PostgreSQL logical
  replication (see *Subscriptions* below).

  .. versionchanged:: 2026-06-17 Critical Fixes based on Opus 4.8 Review
    1. [HIGH BUGFIX] Subscriber column `scock_exchange_acronym` → `stock_exchange_acronym` on
       `common.stock_exchange_mw`, renamed in lock-step with the StocksDB publisher (logical
       replication maps columns by name - both sides must match).
    2. [MEDIUM BUGFIX] Deployment metadata corrected: a single PostgreSQL cluster cannot host two
       major versions, so the original "v17.10 on the same cluster as macrodb / stocksdb (v18.1)"
       claim was invalid. Re-documented as a **dedicated v18.1 Aiven service**, which also keeps
       logical replication in the supported publisher-≤-subscriber direction. *(Confirm the actual
       deployed version with ops.)*
    3. [MEDIUM ENHANCEMENT] Schema-layering inversion fixed: enum `instrument_kind` moved
       `private` → `common`, since `common.strategy_mw` / `common.strategy_universe_mw` (and the
       fact tables) depend on it - a `common` object must not depend on a `private` type.
    4. [MEDIUM ENHANCEMENT] `pnl_daily_tx` gains `ck_pnl_net` (`net_pnl = gross_pnl − total_charges`)
       and non-negativity checks; documented the publisher **no-hard-DELETE contract** that keeps
       the `ON DELETE RESTRICT` FKs from local facts into subscription tables from stalling
       replication apply.
    5. [LOW ENHANCEMENT] Reworded the previously self-contradictory note on subscription-table FKs
       (see *Foreign Keys & Replication* below).

  > **⚠ Reconstruction note (2026-06-17):** the *local* trading tables in this file
  > (`broker_mw`, `account_mw`, `strategy_mw`, `strategy_allocation_mw`,
  > `strategy_universe_mw`, `risk_rule_mw`, and all `private.*_tx` facts) were
  > rebuilt from the design-review model. The five **subscription** tables
  > (`currency_mw`, `securities_mw`, `securities_exchange_symbol_mw`,
  > `stock_exchange_mw`, `derivative_contract_mw`) are reproduced at exact
  > publisher column-shape fidelity. Please diff the local-table column set against
  > your canonical source before applying.

  ## Schema Layout

  | Schema    | Purpose                                                                 |
  |:----------|:------------------------------------------------------------------------|
  | `public`  | Bootstrap / operational meta (data sources).                            |
  | `common`  | Subscription reference data + local trading masters.                    |
  | `private` | Append-mostly trading facts (signals, orders, executions, P&L, audit).  |
  | `dev`     | Developer / auditor user-defined functions only - *no tables*.          |

  ## Naming Conventions

  | Suffix | Meaning                              |
  |:-------|:-------------------------------------|
  | `*_mw` | Master / world-scope reference table |
  | `*_tx` | Transactional / fact table           |

  ## Logical Replication (Subscriptions)

  This database is a pure **subscriber** for reference data. `INSERT / UPDATE /
  DELETE` are revoked from `PUBLIC` on every subscription table.

  | Subscription                     | Source Publication           | Source DB  | Tables                                                       |
  |:---------------------------------|:-----------------------------|:-----------|:-------------------------------------------------------------|
  | `macrodb_currency_reference`     | `macrodb_currency_table`     | `macrodb`  | `common.currency_mw`                                         |
  | `stocksdb_securities_reference`  | `stocksdb_securities_table`  | `stocksdb` | `common.securities_mw`, `common.securities_exchange_symbol_mw` |
  | `stocksdb_exchange_reference`    | `stocksdb_exchange_table`    | `stocksdb` | `common.stock_exchange_mw`                                   |
  | `stocksdb_derivative_reference`  | `stocksdb_derivative_table`  | `stocksdb` | `common.derivative_contract_mw`                             |

  Currency is subscribed directly from MacroDB; the geography hierarchy is **not**
  required here, so exchange geography columns (`stock_exchange_country_id`,
  `registered_city_code`) are carried as plain values with no parent table.

  ## Foreign Keys & Replication  *(ENHANCEMENT 2026-06-17 - reworded)*

  Two distinct rules, previously conflated:

  1. **Among subscription tables:** the replicated reference tables carry **no
     foreign keys to one another** - the publisher-side FKs are dropped on this
     subscriber because logical replication does not guarantee table-apply order,
     and an unresolved cross-table FK would fail apply. Hence `securities_mw`,
     `stock_exchange_mw`, `derivative_contract_mw`, etc. expose their cross-references
     (`isin_data_source_id`, `underlying_isin`, `market_identifier_code`, …) as
     **plain columns**.
  2. **From local facts into subscription tables:** local trading tables *do*
     reference the subscription tables via ordinary FKs (e.g.
     `signal_tx.ses_primary_id → securities_exchange_symbol_mw`). These use
     `ON DELETE RESTRICT`, which is the correct, protective behaviour for an
     audit-grade trading store - a referenced security/contract must not silently
     vanish from under historical trades.

  > **No-hard-DELETE contract (publisher side):** because of rule (2), upstream
  > (`stocksdb` / `macrodb`) **must retire reference rows logically (soft-delete /
  > corporate action), never hard-`DELETE`**. A replicated `DELETE` of a row that a
  > local fact references would otherwise stall this subscriber's `apply` worker
  > against the `RESTRICT` constraint. Retirement signals: `stock_exchange_mw.operational_to`,
  > and `corporate_actions_mw` events (e.g. `DELISTING`) on the StocksDB side.

  ## Custom Enum Types (PostgreSQL - Not Representable in DBML Free Tier)

  | Type                          | Used in                                                                                |
  |:------------------------------|:---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
  | `common.broker_status`        | `common.broker_mw.broker_status`                                                       |
  | `common.account_status`       | `common.account_mw.account_status`                                                     |
  | `common.strategy_stage`       | `common.strategy_mw.strategy_stage`                                                    |
  | `common.instrument_kind`      | `common.strategy_mw`, `common.strategy_universe_mw`, `signal_tx`, `order_tx`, `position_snapshot_tx` · **[ENHANCEMENT 2026-06-17] moved from `private`** |
  | `common.timeframe_value`      | `common.strategy_mw.base_timeframe`                                                    |
  | `common.allocation_policy`    | `common.strategy_allocation_mw.allocation_policy`                                      |
  | `common.risk_scope`           | `common.risk_rule_mw.risk_scope`                                                       |
  | `common.signal_source`        | `private.signal_tx.signal_source`                                                      |
  | `common.execution_mode`       | `private.signal_tx`, `private.order_tx` (LIVE / PAPER / BACKTEST)                      |
  | `common.order_side`           | `private.signal_tx`, `private.order_tx` (BUY / SELL)                                   |
  | `common.order_type`           | `private.order_tx.order_type` (MARKET / LIMIT / SL / SL_M)                             |
  | `common.order_status`         | `private.order_tx.order_status`                                                        |

  Enum columns are represented as `varchar` in this diagram.
  '''
}

// ============================================================================
// public schema - operational bootstrap
// ============================================================================

table public.data_source_mw {
  data_source_id   char(5)      [pk]              // pk_data_source_id
  data_source_name varchar(64)  [not null, unique] // uq_data_source_name
  data_source_desc varchar(256) [not null]
  data_source_uri  varchar(128) [not null, unique] // uq_data_source_uri

  note: '''
  ## Data Source Master (`_mw`)

  Bootstrap reference of external data sources used by locally-mastered trading
  tables (e.g. broker API endpoints).

  > **Note:** `data_source_uri` must store a bare base URL only - never a query
  > string or an embedded credential / token.

  ### Referenced By

  - **`common.broker_mw`** - `fk_broker_data_source`
  '''
}

// ============================================================================
// common schema - subscription reference tables (read-only, replicated)
// (column shapes match the publishers exactly; FKs among them are dropped)
// ============================================================================

table common.currency_mw {
  currency_code     char(3)     [pk]               // pk_currency_code
  currency_name     varchar(64) [not null, unique]  // uq_currency_name
  currency_symbol   varchar(16) [unique]            // uq_currency_symbol
  currency_type     char(1)     [not null]
  currency_subtype  char(1)
  n_decimals        integer     [not null, default: 2]
  minor_unit_name   varchar(32)
  minor_unit_symbol varchar(16)
  minor_unit_factor integer

  note: '''
  ## Currency Reference (`_mw`) - MacroDB Subscription

  Read-only ISO 4217 currency reference. Populated via subscription
  `macrodb_currency_reference` from `macrodb_currency_table`. FK constraints
  omitted on the subscriber side. `INSERT / UPDATE / DELETE` revoked from `PUBLIC`.

  ### Referenced By (local FKs)

  - **`common.account_mw`** - `fk_account_base_currency` (base/settlement currency)
  '''
}

table common.securities_mw {
  security_isin_code   char(12)     [pk]        // pk_security_isin_code
  security_description  varchar(255) [not null]
  security_issuer_name  varchar(255)
  security_issuer_type  varchar(64)              // enum: common.security_issue_type (StocksDB-defined)
  isin_data_source_id   char(5)      [not null]  // plain column - data_source_mw not subscribed (no FK)

  indexes {
    security_issuer_type [name: 'ix_securities_mw_security_issuer_type']
  }

  note: '''
  ## Securities Reference (`_mw`) - StocksDB Subscription

  Read-only securities master subscribed from StocksDB publication
  `stocksdb_securities_table`. `isin_data_source_id` is a **plain column** (no FK)
  because `data_source_mw` is not replicated here. `INSERT / UPDATE / DELETE`
  revoked from `PUBLIC`.

  ### Referenced By (local FKs into this subscription table)

  - **`common.securities_exchange_symbol_mw`** - logical only (subscription table, no FK)
  '''
}

table common.securities_exchange_symbol_mw {
  ses_primary_id         integer      [pk]        // pk_securities_exchange_symbol_id · replicated value (no identity on subscriber)
  security_isin_code     char(12)     [not null]  // plain - subscription table (no FK)
  market_identifier_code char(4)      [not null]  // plain - subscription table (no FK)
  exchange_symbol        varchar(32)  [not null]
  exchange_symbol_name   varchar(255) [not null]
  symbol_series_code     varchar(16)
  ses_data_source_id     char(5)      [not null]  // plain - subscription table (no FK)
  created_on             timestamptz  [not null]  // default omitted on subscriber - value arrives via replication

  indexes {
    market_identifier_code [name: 'ix_securities_exchange_symbol_mw_market_identifier_code']
    symbol_series_code      [name: 'ix_securities_exchange_symbol_mw_symbol_series_code']
    exchange_symbol         [name: 'ix_securities_exchange_symbol_mw_exchange_symbol']
    (security_isin_code, market_identifier_code, exchange_symbol, exchange_symbol_name) [unique, name: 'uq_exchange_symbol']
  }

  note: '''
  ## Securities Exchange Symbol Mapping (`_mw`) - StocksDB Subscription

  Read-only ISIN→symbol-per-exchange bridge subscribed from
  `stocksdb_securities_table`. `ses_primary_id` is the platform-wide equity
  trading grain; its identity sequence lives on the StocksDB publisher, here it is
  a plain `integer` PK holding the replicated value. All cross-references are plain
  columns (no FKs). `INSERT / UPDATE / DELETE` revoked from `PUBLIC`.

  ### Referenced By (local FKs into this subscription table)

  - **`common.strategy_universe_mw`** - `fk_universe_ses`
  - **`private.signal_tx`** - `fk_signal_ses`
  - **`private.order_tx`** - `fk_order_ses`
  - **`private.position_snapshot_tx`** - `fk_snapshot_ses`
  '''
}

table common.stock_exchange_mw {
  market_identifier_code    char(4)     [pk]        // pk_market_identifier_code
  operating_mic_code        char(4)     [not null]
  legal_exchange_name       varchar(64) [not null]
  stock_exchange_acronym    varchar(16)              // [BUGFIX 2026-06-17] renamed from scock_exchange_acronym (lock-step w/ StocksDB publisher)
  stock_exchange_country_id char(3)     [not null]  // plain - geography not subscribed (no FK)
  registered_city_code      char(5)                  // plain - geography not subscribed (no FK)
  trading_currency_code     char(3)     [not null]  // plain - subscription table (no FK)
  operational_from          date        [not null]
  operational_to            date
  data_source_id            char(5)     [not null]  // plain - subscription table (no FK)

  indexes {
    (stock_exchange_country_id, legal_exchange_name) [unique, name: 'uq_stock_exchange_name']
  }

  note: '''
  ## Stock Exchange Reference (`_mw`) - StocksDB Subscription

  Read-only exchange master subscribed from `stocksdb_exchange_table`. Geography
  and currency references are plain columns (those parents are not replicated here).
  `INSERT / UPDATE / DELETE` revoked from `PUBLIC`.

  > **[BUGFIX 2026-06-17]** The mis-spelled `scock_exchange_acronym` is corrected to
  > `stock_exchange_acronym`. Because replication matches columns by name, apply the
  > `RENAME COLUMN` here in lock-step with the StocksDB publisher (disable subscription
  > → rename both sides → enable + `REFRESH PUBLICATION`).

  ### Referenced By (local FKs into this subscription table)

  - **`common.derivative_contract_mw`** - logical only (subscription table, no FK)
  '''
}

table common.derivative_contract_mw {
  derivative_contract_id  bigint        [pk]        // pk_derivative_contract_id · replicated value (no identity on subscriber)
  underlying_type         varchar       [not null]  // enum: common.underlying_type (INDEX, EQUITY)
  underlying_isin         char(12)                   // plain - subscription table (no FK)
  underlying_index_id     integer                    // plain - market_index_mw not subscribed (no FK)
  instrument_type         varchar       [not null]  // enum: common.derivative_instrument_type
  option_type             varchar                    // enum: common.option_type (CALL, PUT) · NULL for futures
  strike_price            numeric(21,5)              // NULL for futures
  expiry_date             date          [not null]
  market_identifier_code  char(4)       [not null]  // plain - subscription table (no FK)
  tradable_symbol         varchar(64)   [not null]
  lot_size                integer
  tick_size               numeric(21,5)
  contract_data_source_id char(5)       [not null]  // plain - subscription table (no FK)
  created_on              timestamptz   [not null]

  indexes {
    (market_identifier_code, instrument_type, underlying_type, underlying_isin, underlying_index_id, expiry_date, option_type, strike_price) [unique, name: 'uq_derivative_contract']
  }

  note: '''
  ## Derivative Contract Reference (`_mw`) - StocksDB Subscription

  Read-only option/future contract master subscribed from
  `stocksdb_derivative_table`. The polymorphic underlying (`underlying_isin` /
  `underlying_index_id`) and exchange reference are plain columns - the publisher-side
  FKs and check constraints are enforced upstream and dropped here.
  `INSERT / UPDATE / DELETE` revoked from `PUBLIC`.

  ### Referenced By (local FKs into this subscription table)

  - **`common.strategy_universe_mw`** - `fk_universe_contract`
  - **`private.signal_tx`** - `fk_signal_contract`
  - **`private.order_tx`** - `fk_order_contract`
  - **`private.position_snapshot_tx`** - `fk_snapshot_contract`
  '''
}

// ============================================================================
// common schema - local trading masters  (reconstructed from design model)
// ============================================================================

table common.broker_mw {
  broker_id           integer      [pk, increment]                                                // pk_broker_id · generated always as identity
  broker_name         varchar(64)  [not null, unique]                                              // uq_broker_name
  broker_short_code   varchar(16)  [not null, unique]                                              // uq_broker_short_code
  broker_status       varchar(16)  [not null]                                                      // enum: common.broker_status (ACTIVE, SUSPENDED, DECOMMISSIONED)
  supports_paper      boolean      [not null, default: false]
  api_base_uri        varchar(128)
  api_docs_uri        varchar(128)
  broker_data_source  char(5)      [ref: > public.data_source_mw.data_source_id]                  // fk_broker_data_source · nullable · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  created_on          timestamptz  [not null, default: `now()`]

  note: '''
  ## Broker Master (`_mw`) - local

  Brokers whose API platforms execute orders. `broker_status` gates whether new
  accounts/orders may be routed; `supports_paper` flags brokers that expose a
  paper-trading endpoint.

  ### Referenced By

  - **`common.account_mw`** - `fk_account_broker`
  '''
}

table common.account_mw {
  account_uuid       char(10)     [pk]                                                            // pk_account_uuid
  broker_id          integer      [not null, ref: > common.broker_mw.broker_id]                  // fk_account_broker · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  account_label      varchar(64)  [not null]
  broker_account_ref varchar(64)  [not null]
  base_currency_code char(3)      [not null, ref: > common.currency_mw.currency_code]            // fk_account_base_currency · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  account_status     varchar(16)  [not null]                                                      // enum: common.account_status (ACTIVE, FROZEN, CLOSED)
  opened_on          date
  created_on         timestamptz  [not null, default: `now()`]

  indexes {
    (broker_id, broker_account_ref) [unique, name: 'uq_account_broker_ref'] // one local account per broker-side account id
  }

  note: '''
  ## Trading Account Master (`_mw`) - local

  A funded trading account at a broker. `broker_account_ref` is the broker-side
  account identifier; `base_currency_code` is the settlement currency (subscribed
  from MacroDB).

  ### Parents

  - **`common.broker_mw`** - `fk_account_broker`
  - **`common.currency_mw`** - `fk_account_base_currency`

  ### Referenced By

  - `common.strategy_allocation_mw`, `common.risk_rule_mw`,
    `private.signal_tx`, `private.order_tx`, `private.position_snapshot_tx`,
    `private.pnl_daily_tx`, `private.circuit_breaker_tx`.
  '''
}

table common.strategy_mw {
  strategy_uuid       char(8)      [pk]                                                            // pk_strategy_uuid
  strategy_name       varchar(64)  [not null, unique]                                              // uq_strategy_name
  strategy_stage      varchar(16)  [not null]                                                      // enum: common.strategy_stage (DEV, BACKTEST, PAPER, LIVE, RETIRED)
  instrument_kind     varchar(16)  [not null]                                                      // enum: common.instrument_kind · [ENHANCEMENT 2026-06-17] moved private→common
  base_timeframe      varchar(8)                                                                   // enum: common.timeframe_value
  strategy_description varchar(255)
  created_on          timestamptz  [not null, default: `now()`]

  note: '''
  ## Strategy Master (`_mw`) - local

  A trading strategy. `strategy_stage` tracks its lifecycle; `instrument_kind`
  declares the asset class it trades.

  > **[ENHANCEMENT 2026-06-17]** `instrument_kind` now references the enum
  > `common.instrument_kind` (relocated from `private`) - a `common` table must not
  > depend on a `private` type.

  ### Referenced By

  - `common.strategy_allocation_mw`, `common.strategy_universe_mw`,
    `private.signal_tx`, `private.order_tx`, `private.pnl_daily_tx`,
    `common.risk_rule_mw`, `private.circuit_breaker_tx`.
  '''
}

table common.strategy_allocation_mw {
  allocation_id     integer      [pk, increment]                                                  // pk_allocation_id · generated always as identity
  strategy_uuid     char(8)      [not null, ref: > common.strategy_mw.strategy_uuid]              // fk_allocation_strategy · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  account_uuid      char(10)     [not null, ref: > common.account_mw.account_uuid]                // fk_allocation_account · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  allocation_policy varchar(24)  [not null]                                                        // enum: common.allocation_policy (FIXED_CAPITAL, PCT_EQUITY, RISK_PARITY)
  allocation_value  numeric(21,5)                                                                  // absolute capital (FIXED_CAPITAL)
  allocation_pct    numeric(5,2)                                                                   // percent of equity (PCT_EQUITY) · 0 < pct <= 100
  is_enabled        boolean      [not null, default: true]
  effective_from    date         [not null]
  created_on        timestamptz  [not null, default: `now()`]

  indexes {
    (strategy_uuid, account_uuid, effective_from) [unique, name: 'uq_allocation_strategy_account']
  }

  note: '''
  ## Strategy Capital Allocation (`_mw`) - local

  Capital assigned to a strategy on an account under a given policy.

  ### Parents

  - **`common.strategy_mw`** - `fk_allocation_strategy`
  - **`common.account_mw`** - `fk_allocation_account`

  ### Check Constraints

  - `ck_allocation_policy_fields` - `FIXED_CAPITAL` ⇒ `allocation_value` set and
    `allocation_pct` NULL; `PCT_EQUITY` ⇒ `allocation_pct` set in `(0, 100]` and
    `allocation_value` NULL.
  '''
}

table common.strategy_universe_mw {
  universe_id            integer      [pk, increment]                                              // pk_universe_id · generated always as identity
  strategy_uuid          char(8)      [not null, ref: > common.strategy_mw.strategy_uuid]          // fk_universe_strategy · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  instrument_kind        varchar(16)  [not null]                                                   // enum: common.instrument_kind · [ENHANCEMENT 2026-06-17] moved private→common
  ses_primary_id         integer      [ref: > common.securities_exchange_symbol_mw.ses_primary_id] // fk_universe_ses · nullable · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  derivative_contract_id bigint       [ref: > common.derivative_contract_mw.derivative_contract_id]// fk_universe_contract · nullable · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  is_enabled             boolean      [not null, default: true]
  created_on             timestamptz  [not null, default: `now()`]

  indexes {
    (strategy_uuid, ses_primary_id, derivative_contract_id) [unique, name: 'uq_universe_instrument'] // UNIQUE NULLS NOT DISTINCT
  }

  note: '''
  ## Strategy Tradable Universe (`_mw`) - local

  The set of instruments a strategy is permitted to trade. The instrument is
  polymorphic - either an equity symbol (`ses_primary_id`) or a derivative contract
  (`derivative_contract_id`), matching `instrument_kind`. Both FKs point **into
  subscription tables** (see *Foreign Keys & Replication*).

  ### Parents

  - **`common.strategy_mw`** - `fk_universe_strategy`
  - **`common.securities_exchange_symbol_mw`** (subscription) - `fk_universe_ses`
  - **`common.derivative_contract_mw`** (subscription) - `fk_universe_contract`

  ### Check Constraints

  - `ck_universe_instrument_xor` - exactly one of `ses_primary_id` /
    `derivative_contract_id` is set, consistent with `instrument_kind`.
  '''
}

table common.risk_rule_mw {
  risk_rule_id    integer      [pk, increment]                                                    // pk_risk_rule_id · generated always as identity
  risk_scope      varchar(16)  [not null]                                                          // enum: common.risk_scope (GLOBAL, ACCOUNT, STRATEGY)
  account_uuid    char(10)     [ref: > common.account_mw.account_uuid]                            // fk_risk_account · nullable · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  strategy_uuid   char(8)      [ref: > common.strategy_mw.strategy_uuid]                          // fk_risk_strategy · nullable · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  rule_name       varchar(64)  [not null]
  threshold_unit  varchar(8)   [not null]                                                          // PCT | ABS | COUNT
  threshold_value numeric(21,5) [not null]
  is_active       boolean      [not null, default: true]
  created_on      timestamptz  [not null, default: `now()`]

  note: '''
  ## Risk Rule Master (`_mw`) - local

  Risk limits applied globally, per account, or per strategy (e.g. max daily loss,
  max position count, max gross exposure). `threshold_unit` qualifies
  `threshold_value` (percent / absolute / count).

  ### Parents

  - **`common.account_mw`** - `fk_risk_account` (nullable)
  - **`common.strategy_mw`** - `fk_risk_strategy` (nullable)

  ### Check Constraints

  - `ck_risk_scope_target` - `ACCOUNT` ⇒ `account_uuid` set; `STRATEGY` ⇒
    `strategy_uuid` set; `GLOBAL` ⇒ both NULL.
  - `ck_risk_threshold_unit` - `threshold_unit IN ('PCT','ABS','COUNT')`.

  ### Referenced By

  - **`private.circuit_breaker_tx`** - `fk_breaker_risk_rule`
  '''
}

// ============================================================================
// private schema - trading facts (append-mostly)
// ============================================================================

table private.signal_tx {
  signal_uuid            uuid          [pk]                                                         // pk_signal_uuid
  account_uuid           char(10)      [not null, ref: > common.account_mw.account_uuid]            // fk_signal_account · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  strategy_uuid          char(8)       [not null, ref: > common.strategy_mw.strategy_uuid]          // fk_signal_strategy · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  instrument_kind        varchar(16)   [not null]                                                   // enum: common.instrument_kind
  ses_primary_id         integer       [ref: > common.securities_exchange_symbol_mw.ses_primary_id] // fk_signal_ses · nullable · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  derivative_contract_id bigint        [ref: > common.derivative_contract_mw.derivative_contract_id]// fk_signal_contract · nullable · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  signal_source          varchar(16)   [not null]                                                   // enum: common.signal_source (RULE_ENGINE, ML_MODEL, MANUAL, EXTERNAL)
  execution_mode         varchar(12)   [not null]                                                   // enum: common.execution_mode (LIVE, PAPER, BACKTEST)
  order_side             varchar(4)    [not null]                                                   // enum: common.order_side (BUY, SELL)
  signal_strength        numeric(12,6)
  target_price           numeric(21,5)
  stoploss_price         numeric(21,5)
  signal_time            timestamptz   [not null]
  payload                jsonb
  created_on             timestamptz   [not null, default: `now()`]

  indexes {
    (strategy_uuid, signal_time) [name: 'ix_signal_strategy_time']
    (account_uuid, signal_time)  [name: 'ix_signal_account_time']
  }

  note: '''
  ## Trading Signal (`_tx`) - local fact

  A strategy-generated trade intent. The instrument is polymorphic (equity symbol
  or derivative contract); both FKs point into subscription tables. `execution_mode`
  isolates LIVE / PAPER / BACKTEST streams within one table. `payload` retains the
  raw generator output (features, model scores) as `jsonb`.

  ### Parents

  - **`common.account_mw`** - `fk_signal_account`
  - **`common.strategy_mw`** - `fk_signal_strategy`
  - **`common.securities_exchange_symbol_mw`** (subscription) - `fk_signal_ses`
  - **`common.derivative_contract_mw`** (subscription) - `fk_signal_contract`

  ### Check Constraints

  - `ck_signal_instrument_xor` - exactly one instrument ref set, matching `instrument_kind`.

  ### Referenced By

  - **`private.order_tx`** - `fk_order_signal`
  '''
}

table private.order_tx {
  order_uuid             uuid          [pk]                                                         // pk_order_uuid
  signal_uuid            uuid          [ref: > private.signal_tx.signal_uuid]                       // fk_order_signal · nullable (manual orders) · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  account_uuid           char(10)      [not null, ref: > common.account_mw.account_uuid]            // fk_order_account · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  strategy_uuid          char(8)       [ref: > common.strategy_mw.strategy_uuid]                    // fk_order_strategy · nullable · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  instrument_kind        varchar(16)   [not null]                                                   // enum: common.instrument_kind
  ses_primary_id         integer       [ref: > common.securities_exchange_symbol_mw.ses_primary_id] // fk_order_ses · nullable · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  derivative_contract_id bigint        [ref: > common.derivative_contract_mw.derivative_contract_id]// fk_order_contract · nullable · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  execution_mode         varchar(12)   [not null]                                                   // enum: common.execution_mode
  order_side             varchar(4)    [not null]                                                   // enum: common.order_side
  order_type             varchar(8)    [not null]                                                   // enum: common.order_type (MARKET, LIMIT, SL, SL_M)
  product_type           varchar(16)
  order_quantity         integer       [not null]
  limit_price            numeric(21,5)
  trigger_price          numeric(21,5)
  order_status           varchar(20)   [not null]                                                   // enum: common.order_status
  broker_order_ref       varchar(64)
  placed_time            timestamptz   [not null]
  payload                jsonb
  created_on             timestamptz   [not null, default: `now()`]

  indexes {
    (account_uuid, placed_time) [name: 'ix_order_account_time']
    broker_order_ref            [name: 'ix_order_broker_ref']
  }

  note: '''
  ## Order (`_tx`) - local fact

  An order routed to a broker (or simulated for PAPER / BACKTEST). Links back to its
  originating signal (nullable - manual orders have none). The
  `signal_uuid → signal_tx` FK uses `ON DELETE RESTRICT`, preserving lineage.

  ### Parents

  - **`private.signal_tx`** - `fk_order_signal` (nullable)
  - **`common.account_mw`** - `fk_order_account`
  - **`common.strategy_mw`** - `fk_order_strategy` (nullable)
  - **`common.securities_exchange_symbol_mw`** (subscription) - `fk_order_ses`
  - **`common.derivative_contract_mw`** (subscription) - `fk_order_contract`

  ### Check Constraints

  - `ck_order_instrument_xor` - exactly one instrument ref set, matching `instrument_kind`.
  - `ck_order_quantity` - `order_quantity > 0`.
  - `ck_order_prices` - `limit_price` required for LIMIT/SL; `trigger_price` required for SL/SL_M.

  > **Application invariant (trigger-enforced, not a DBML FK):** when `signal_uuid`
  > is set, `order_tx.account_uuid` / `strategy_uuid` must equal the parent signal's.

  ### Referenced By

  - **`private.execution_tx`** - `fk_execution_order`
  '''
}

table private.execution_tx {
  execution_uuid       uuid          [pk]                                                           // pk_execution_uuid
  order_uuid           uuid          [not null, ref: > private.order_tx.order_uuid]                 // fk_execution_order · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  execution_mode       varchar(12)   [not null]                                                     // enum: common.execution_mode
  filled_quantity      integer       [not null]
  fill_price           numeric(21,5) [not null]
  gross_amount         numeric(21,5)
  brokerage            numeric(21,5)
  exchange_charges     numeric(21,5)
  taxes                numeric(21,5)
  net_amount           numeric(21,5)
  broker_execution_ref varchar(64)
  exchange_time        timestamptz   [not null]
  created_on           timestamptz   [not null, default: `now()`]

  indexes {
    (order_uuid, exchange_time) [name: 'ix_execution_order_time']
  }

  note: '''
  ## Execution / Fill (`_tx`) - local fact

  A (partial) fill against an order. `net_amount` is the signed settlement cashflow
  (negative on buys, positive on sells, net of charges).

  ### Parents

  - **`private.order_tx`** - `fk_execution_order`

  ### Check Constraints

  - `ck_execution_quantity` - `filled_quantity > 0` and `fill_price >= 0`.
  - `ck_execution_charges` - `brokerage`, `exchange_charges`, `taxes` ≥ 0 when present.
  '''
}

table private.position_snapshot_tx {
  snapshot_id            bigint        [pk, increment]                                              // pk_position_snapshot_id · generated always as identity
  account_uuid           char(10)      [not null, ref: > common.account_mw.account_uuid]            // fk_snapshot_account · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  instrument_kind        varchar(16)   [not null]                                                   // enum: common.instrument_kind
  ses_primary_id         integer       [ref: > common.securities_exchange_symbol_mw.ses_primary_id] // fk_snapshot_ses · nullable · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  derivative_contract_id bigint        [ref: > common.derivative_contract_mw.derivative_contract_id]// fk_snapshot_contract · nullable · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  net_quantity           integer       [not null]
  average_price          numeric(21,5)
  mark_price             numeric(21,5)
  realized_pnl           numeric(21,5)
  unrealized_pnl         numeric(21,5)
  snapshot_time          timestamptz   [not null]
  created_on             timestamptz   [not null, default: `now()`]

  indexes {
    (account_uuid, ses_primary_id, derivative_contract_id, snapshot_time) [unique, name: 'uq_position_snapshot'] // UNIQUE NULLS NOT DISTINCT
  }

  note: '''
  ## Position Snapshot (`_tx`) - local fact

  Point-in-time net position per account per instrument. `net_quantity` may be
  negative (short). Instrument polymorphic via subscription-table FKs.

  ### Parents

  - **`common.account_mw`** - `fk_snapshot_account`
  - **`common.securities_exchange_symbol_mw`** (subscription) - `fk_snapshot_ses`
  - **`common.derivative_contract_mw`** (subscription) - `fk_snapshot_contract`

  ### Check Constraints

  - `ck_snapshot_instrument_xor` - exactly one instrument ref set, matching `instrument_kind`.
  '''
}

table private.pnl_daily_tx {
  pnl_id         bigint        [pk, increment]                                                      // pk_pnl_daily_id · generated always as identity
  account_uuid   char(10)      [not null, ref: > common.account_mw.account_uuid]                    // fk_pnl_account · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  strategy_uuid  char(8)       [ref: > common.strategy_mw.strategy_uuid]                            // fk_pnl_strategy · nullable (account-level rollup) · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  trade_date     date          [not null]
  gross_pnl      numeric(21,5) [not null]
  total_charges  numeric(21,5) [not null]
  net_pnl        numeric(21,5) [not null]
  realized_pnl   numeric(21,5)
  unrealized_pnl numeric(21,5)
  trade_count    integer
  created_on     timestamptz   [not null, default: `now()`]

  indexes {
    (account_uuid, strategy_uuid, trade_date) [unique, name: 'uq_pnl_daily'] // UNIQUE NULLS NOT DISTINCT - one row per account/strategy/day
  }

  note: '''
  ## Daily P&L (`_tx`) - local fact

  End-of-day profit and loss per account (optionally per strategy).

  ### Parents

  - **`common.account_mw`** - `fk_pnl_account`
  - **`common.strategy_mw`** - `fk_pnl_strategy` (nullable for account-level rollups)

  ### Check Constraints *(ENHANCEMENT 2026-06-17)*

  - `ck_pnl_net` - `net_pnl = gross_pnl − total_charges` (enforces the accounting identity).
  - `ck_pnl_charges` - `total_charges >= 0`.
  - `ck_pnl_count` - `trade_count IS NULL OR trade_count >= 0`.
  '''
}

table private.circuit_breaker_tx {
  breaker_id     bigint        [pk, increment]                                                      // pk_circuit_breaker_id · generated always as identity
  risk_rule_id   integer       [ref: > common.risk_rule_mw.risk_rule_id]                            // fk_breaker_risk_rule · nullable · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  account_uuid   char(10)      [ref: > common.account_mw.account_uuid]                              // fk_breaker_account · nullable · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  strategy_uuid  char(8)       [ref: > common.strategy_mw.strategy_uuid]                            // fk_breaker_strategy · nullable · on update cascade · on delete restrict
  breaker_scope  varchar(16)   [not null]                                                            // GLOBAL | ACCOUNT | STRATEGY
  trigger_reason varchar(255)  [not null]
  threshold_value numeric(21,5)
  observed_value  numeric(21,5)
  triggered_at   timestamptz   [not null]
  released_at    timestamptz
  created_on     timestamptz   [not null, default: `now()`]

  indexes {
    (triggered_at) [name: 'ix_breaker_triggered_at']
  }

  note: '''
  ## Circuit Breaker Event (`_tx`) - local fact

  Records a risk circuit-breaker firing (e.g. daily-loss limit hit) and its
  optional release. Scope mirrors the originating `risk_rule_mw`.

  ### Parents

  - **`common.risk_rule_mw`** - `fk_breaker_risk_rule` (nullable)
  - **`common.account_mw`** - `fk_breaker_account` (nullable)
  - **`common.strategy_mw`** - `fk_breaker_strategy` (nullable)

  ### Check Constraints

  - `ck_breaker_release` - `released_at IS NULL OR released_at >= triggered_at`.
  '''
}

table private.audit_log_tx {
  audit_id       bigint       [pk, increment]      // pk_audit_log_id · generated always as identity
  entity_name    varchar(64)  [not null]
  entity_pk      varchar(64)
  audit_action   varchar(32)  [not null]            // INSERT | UPDATE | DELETE | LOGIN | CONFIG | ...
  actor          varchar(64)
  change_payload jsonb
  logged_at      timestamptz  [not null, default: `now()`]

  indexes {
    (entity_name, logged_at) [name: 'ix_audit_entity_time']
  }

  note: '''
  ## Immutable Audit Log (`_tx`) - local, append-only

  Tamper-evident audit trail. Deliberately carries **no foreign keys** so a logged
  reference can never be blocked or cascaded by parent-row changes - the entity is
  identified by (`entity_name`, `entity_pk`) text.

  > **Immutability:** `UPDATE` and `DELETE` are revoked from `PUBLIC` and additionally
  > blocked by a `BEFORE UPDATE OR DELETE` trigger that raises an exception. Rows are
  > insert-only; `logged_at` defaults to `now()`.
  '''
}

// ============================================================================
// table groups - layout clusters for dbdiagram.io
// ============================================================================

tablegroup data_sources {
  public.data_source_mw
}

tablegroup subscribed_reference {
  common.currency_mw
  common.securities_mw
  common.securities_exchange_symbol_mw
  common.stock_exchange_mw
  common.derivative_contract_mw
}

tablegroup trading_masters {
  common.broker_mw
  common.account_mw
  common.strategy_mw
  common.strategy_allocation_mw
  common.strategy_universe_mw
  common.risk_rule_mw
}

tablegroup trading_facts {
  private.signal_tx
  private.order_tx
  private.execution_tx
  private.position_snapshot_tx
  private.pnl_daily_tx
  private.circuit_breaker_tx
  private.audit_log_tx
}
